success.question_text: How many kilolitres of water will it hold?

stimulus_2.text:

A tank is a rectangular prism 3 metres long, 2 metres wide and 1.5 metres deep.

success.question_text: What is the area of the shaded cross?

success.question_text: How much more rain needs to fall to fill the tank?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Capacity and Volume

stimulus_1.text: One day Mr Richardson estimated that the school’s water tank was one-quarter full.

stimulus_3.text:
That night there was a thunderstorm and 15 millimetres was recorded on the school’s rain gauge.

The next morning Mr Richardson announced that the tank was now half full of water.

success.question_text: If one pumpkin is 800 grams heavier than the other, what is the mass of the heavier pumpkin?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Mass

stimulus_2.text: The total mass of two pumpkins is 8.4 kilograms.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Use the conversion 1000 grams (g) = 1 kilogram (kg). To change grams to kilograms, divide by 1000. To change kilograms to grams, multiply by 1000.

success.question_text: If the breadth of the rectangle is 20 centimetres, what is the area of the rectangle in square centimetres?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Area

success.question_text: Which statement is correct?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Problem Solving

stimulus_1.text: Some scarves are hanging on a straight piece of rope. The centre of the red scarf is 70 centimetres from the centre of the blue scarf. The centre of the yellow scarf is 40 centimetres from the centre of the red scarf.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Draw a diagram to help solve a problem.

choice_1.label: The blue scarf must be 30 cm from the yellow scarf.

choice_2.label: The blue scarf must be 110 cm from the yellow scarf.

choice_3.label: The blue scarf could be 30 cm or 110 cm from the yellow scarf.

choice_4.label: The blue scarf could be 80 cm or 140 cm from the yellow scarf.

success.question_text:
Enrique needs to cut cubes with side length 4 cm from the rectangular prism.

What is the largest number of cubes he can cut?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Capacity and Volume

stimulus_1.text: A solid rectangular prism is 16 cm long, 8 cm wide and 12 cm high.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The volume of a rectangular prism is found by multiplying the length by the breadth by the height.

success.question_text: If the journey took 1 hour 19 minutes, what time did Kevin reach his destination?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Time

stimulus_2.text:
Kevin’s train was scheduled to depart at 9:27.

The train departed 15 minutes late.

success.question_text:
The surface area of a solid is the total area of all its faces.

What is the difference in the surface area of the two models?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Area

stimulus_1.text: Jemma and Emma take turns in arranging five identical cubes each with side length of 1 cm.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The surface area of a solid is the sum of the areas of each of its faces.

success.question_text: What is the difference between the highest temperature and the lowest temperature during the week?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Tables

stimulus_1.text: The lowest temperature during a day is called the minimum and the highest temperature is called the maximum.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

When you are asked to find differences, use subtraction.

success.question_text:
Branco stopped for a break after a couple of hours.

For how long was Branco stopped?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Graphs

stimulus_1.text:
Branco left his home to travel to his sister’s house. He arrived at her house at 1:30 pm.

His travel graph appears below.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A travel graph shows the distance that a traveller is from a place over time. A horizontal line shows that the distance is not changing and so the traveller is stopped.

stimulus_1.text:
Branco left his home to travel to his sister’s home. He arrived at her house at 1:30 pm.

review_3.column_1_text:
Branco arrived at his sister’s house at 1:30 pm so the distance to her house was 240 kilometres.

stimulus_2.text: Leah travels at a speed of 80 km/h for 45 minutes.

stimulus_1.text: An indoor court has painted lines on the floor.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Follow the rule of order of operations: brackets, then multiplication and division, then addition and subtraction.

success.question_text: If the front wheel turns 20 times, how many times will one of the back wheels turn?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Circumference

stimulus_1.text: Liam’s tricycle has its front wheel bigger than its back wheels. The front wheel has a circumference of 160 centimetres and each of the back wheels have a circumference of 80 centimetres.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

The circumference is the distance around the outside of a circle.

success.question_text: What is the cheapest meat per kilogram?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Measurement Data and Chance / Tables

stimulus_1.text: The table shows the price of four different meats available at Joe’s Deli.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

To find the best buy in a list of products, express each product as a price per the same unit to make it easy to compare the prices.
